                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.001 Moncada/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-01T13:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 1, 1929—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Moncada was inaugurated this morning at an orderly and impressive ceremony on
                    a platform in front of the National Palace. He and President Diaz drove together
                    from the latter’s residence to the palace and after the ceremony the entire
                    party attended a <hi rend="italic">Te Deum</hi> at the Cathedral and then
                    proceeded to the Presidential Palace where there was an informal reception
                    attended by members of both parties. Tonight there will be an inaugural ball.
                    General Beadle, the chief of the <hi rend="italic">guardia</hi>, was responsible
                    for most of the arrangements for the inauguration and the success of these
                    arrangements reflected much credit on his organization.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
